Male. Median lobe long, narrow and curved, with short and wide apical projection, slightly directed posteriad; apical projection of internal sac as long as median lobe of aedeagus, with rather wide and very long, spirally folded flagellum (
Fig. 58
). Each medioapical portion of abdominal tergite VII with moderately long, sharp tubercles and additional fine latero-apical tubercles. Apical margin of abdominal tergite VIII with narrow, moderately long and acute projections, with wide slightly sinuate margin between them (
Fig. 59
). Apical margin of abdominal sternite VIII rounded (
Fig. 60
).

Female. Abdominal tergite VII smooth, without tubercles. Apical margins of abdominal tergite VIII (
Fig. 61
) somewhat truncated. Apical margin of abdominal sternite VIII (
Fig. 62
) rounded.
